```json
{
  "application": "Snakemake",
  "details": {
    "modules": [
      "python/3.4.3",
      "R/3.2.0_gcc-4.4.7",
      "rpy2/2.6.1-R_3.2.0"
    ],
    "resources": {
      "serpentine": "/data/Clinomics/Tools/serpentine2",
      "samplesheet": "Clinomics_pipeline_samplesheet.txt",
      "config": "${SERPENTINE_HOME}/config_common.json",
      "snakefile": "${SERPENTINE_HOME}/workflows/variant_calling/Snakefile",
      "jobscript": "${SERPENTINE_HOME}/jobscript.sh",
      "stats": "serpentine_${NOW}.stats",
      "log": "serpentine_${NOW}.log",
      "cluster": "sbatch -p ccr -e log/{params.rulename}.%j.e -o log/{params.rulename}.%j.o {params.batch}"
    },
    "dependencies": [
      "do_samplesheet2json.R",
      "Snakefile",
      "jobscript.sh"
    ],
    "parameters": {
      "jobname": "cln.{rulename}.{jobid}",
      "cores": 10,
      "threads": 1,
      "jobs": 3000
    }
  }
}
```

This script utilizes the **Snakemake** workflow management system. It leverages several modules including Python, R, and the RPy2 package. It relies on resources such as the Serpentine library, a samplesheet, a configuration file, a Snakefile, a job script, and a cluster submission script. It also uses several parameters for configuring the Snakemake workflow.
